TIRTOUGA.name: Tirtouga
TIRTOUGA.pokedex: This Pokémon inhabited ancient seas. Although it can only crawl, it still comes up onto land in search of prey.

CARRACOSTA.name: Carracosta
CARRACOSTA.pokedex: Carracosta completely devours its prey - bones, shells, and all. Because of this, Carracosta's own shell grows thick and sturdy.

ARCHEN.name: Archen
ARCHEN.pokedex: This Pokémon was successfully restored from a fossil. As research suggested, Archen is unable to fly. But it's very good at jumping.

ARCHEOPS.name: Archeops
ARCHEOPS.pokedex: It needs a running start to take off. If Archeops wants to fly, it first needs to run nearly 25 mph, building speed over a course of about 2.5 miles.

TRUBBISH.name: Trubbish
TRUBBISH.pokedex: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

GARBODOR.name: Garbodor
GARBODOR.pokedex: Consuming garbage makes new kinds of poison gases and liquids inside their bodies.

ZORUA.name: Zorua
ZORUA.pokedex: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.

ZOROARK.name: Zoroark
ZOROARK.pokedex: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

MINCCINO.name: Minccino
MINCCINO.pokedex: These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.

CINCCINO.name: Cinccino
CINCCINO.pokedex: Cinccino's body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks, such as punches.

GOTHITA.name: Gothita
GOTHITA.pokedex: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.

GOTHORITA.name: Gothorita
GOTHORITA.pokedex: According to many old tales, it creates friends for itself by controlling sleeping children on starry nights.

GOTHITELLE.name: Gothitelle
GOTHITELLE.pokedex: They can predict the future from the placement and movement of the stars. They can see Trainers' life spans.

SOLOSIS.name: Solosis
SOLOSIS.pokedex: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

DUOSION.name: Duosion
DUOSION.pokedex: When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.

REUNICLUS.name: Reuniclus
REUNICLUS.pokedex: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

DUCKLETT.name: Ducklett
DUCKLETT.pokedex: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

SWANNA.name: Swanna
SWANNA.pokedex: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

VANILLITE.name: Vanillite
VANILLITE.pokedex: This Pokémon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. It sleeps buried in snow.

VANILLISH.name: Vanillish
VANILLISH.pokedex: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon's habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

VANILLUXE.name: Vanilluxe
VANILLUXE.pokedex: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and, when angry, cause violent blizzards.

DEERLING.name: Deerling
DEERLING.pokedex: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

SAWSBUCK.name: Sawsbuck
SAWSBUCK.pokedex: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.

EMOLGA.name: Emolga
EMOLGA.pokedex: The energy made in its cheeks' electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

KARRABLAST.name: Karrablast
KARRABLAST.pokedex: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking Shelmet.

ESCAVALIER.name: Escavalier
ESCAVALIER.pokedex: These Pokémon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.

FOONGUS.name: Foongus
FOONGUS.pokedex: It lures Pokémon with its pattern that looks just like a Poké Ball, then releases poison spores.

AMOONGUSS.name: Amoonguss
AMOONGUSS.pokedex: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

FRILLISH.name: Frillish
FRILLISH.pokedex: If its veil-like arms stun and wrap a foe, that foe will be dragged miles below the surface, never to return.

JELLICENT.name: Jellicent
JELLICENT.pokedex: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent's habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.

ALOMOMOLA.name: Alomomola
ALOMOMOLA.pokedex: It gently holds injured and weak Pokémon in its fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.

JOLTIK.name: Joltik
JOLTIK.pokedex: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokémon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.

GALVANTULA.name: Galvantula
GALVANTULA.pokedex: Galvantula attacks its foes with the electricity stored in the fur in its abdomen. To protect itself from threats, it uses electrically charged webs.

FERROSEED.name: Ferroseed
FERROSEED.pokedex: It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.

FERROTHORN.name: Ferrothorn
FERROTHORN.pokedex: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.

KLINK.name: Klink
KLINK.pokedex: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

KLANG.name: Klang
KLANG.pokedex: A minigear and big gear comprise its body. If the minigear it launches at a foe doesn't return, it will die.

KLINKLANG.name: Klinklang
KLINKLANG.pokedex: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.

TYNAMO.name: Tynamo
TYNAMO.pokedex: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.

EELEKTRIK.name: Eelektrik
EELEKTRIK.pokedex: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

EELEKTROSS.name: Eelektross
EELEKTROSS.pokedex: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

ELGYEM.name: Elgyem
ELGYEM.pokedex: Rumors of its origin are linked to a UFO crash site in the desert 50 years ago.

BEHEEYEM.name: Beheeyem
BEHEEYEM.pokedex: It uses psychic power to control an opponent's brain and tamper with its memories.

LITWICK.name: Litwick
LITWICK.pokedex: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

LAMPENT.name: Lampent
LAMPENT.pokedex: It arrives near the moment of death and steals spirit from the body.

CHANDELURE.name: Chandelure
CHANDELURE.pokedex: The spirits burned up in its ominous flame lose their way and wander this world forever.

AXEW.name: Axew
AXEW.pokedex: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly.

FRAXURE.name: Fraxure
FRAXURE.pokedex: A broken tusk will not grow back, so it diligently sharpens its tusks on river rocks after the end of a battle.

HAXORUS.name: Haxorus
HAXORUS.pokedex: Their sturdy tusks will stay sharp even if used to cut steel beams. These Pokémon are covered in hard armor.

CUBCHOO.name: Cubchoo
CUBCHOO.pokedex: Their snot is a barometer of health. When healthy, their snot is sticky and the power of their ice moves increases.

BEARTIC.name: Beartic
BEARTIC.pokedex: It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. Cold northern areas are its habitat.

CRYOGONAL.name: Cryogonal
CRYOGONAL.pokedex: When the weather gets hot, these Pokémon turn into water vapor. Cryogonal are almost never seen during summer.

SHELMET.name: Shelmet
SHELMET.pokedex: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.

ACCELGOR.name: Accelgor
ACCELGOR.pokedex: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

STUNFISK.name: Stunfisk
STUNFISK.pokedex: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.

MIENFOO.name: Mienfoo
MIENFOO.pokedex: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

MIENSHAO.name: Mienshao
MIENSHAO.pokedex: Using the long fur on its arms like whips, it launches into combo attacks that, once started, no one can stop.

DRUDDIGON.name: Druddigon
DRUDDIGON.pokedex: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

GOLETT.name: Golett
GOLETT.pokedex: Ancient science fashioned this Pokémon from clay. It's been active for thousands of years.

GOLURK.name: Golurk
GOLURK.pokedex: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

PAWNIARD.name: Pawniard
PAWNIARD.pokedex: Ignoring their injuries, groups attack by sinking the blades that cover their bodies into their prey.

BISHARP.name: Bisharp
BISHARP.pokedex: Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.

BOUFFALANT.name: Bouffalant
BOUFFALANT.pokedex: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

RUFFLET.name: Rufflet
RUFFLET.pokedex: They will challenge anything, even strong opponents, without fear. Their frequent fights help them become stronger.

BRAVIARY.name: Braviary
BRAVIARY.pokedex: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.

VULLABY.name: Vullaby
VULLABY.pokedex: Their wings are too tiny to allow them to fly. They guard their posteriors with bones that were gathered by Mandibuzz.

MANDIBUZZ.name: Mandibuzz
MANDIBUZZ.pokedex: Watching from the sky, they swoop to strike weakened Pokémon on the ground. They decorate themselves with bones.

HEATMOR.name: Heatmor
HEATMOR.pokedex: It draws in air through its tail, transforms it into fire, and uses it like a tongue. It melts Durant and eats them.

DURANT.name: Durant
DURANT.pokedex: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

DEINO.name: Deino
DEINO.pokedex: Lacking sight, it's unaware of its surroundings, so it bumps into things and eats anything that moves.

ZWEILOUS.name: Zweilous
ZWEILOUS.pokedex: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

HYDREIGON.name: Hydreigon
HYDREIGON.pokedex: It responds to movement by attacking. This scary, three-headed Pokémon devours everything in its path!

LARVESTA.name: Larvesta
LARVESTA.pokedex: The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.

VOLCARONA.name: Volcarona
VOLCARONA.pokedex: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona's fire provided a replacement for the sun.

COBALION.name: Cobalion
COBALION.pokedex: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokémon.

TERRAKION.name: Terrakion
TERRAKION.pokedex: Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokémon.

VIRIZION.name: Virizion
VIRIZION.pokedex: Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.

TORNADUS.name: Tornadus
TORNADUS.pokedex: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.

THUNDURUS.name: Thundurus
THUNDURUS.pokedex: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

RESHIRAM.name: Reshiram
RESHIRAM.pokedex: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.

ZEKROM.name: Zekrom
ZEKROM.pokedex: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

LANDORUS.name: Landorus
LANDORUS.pokedex: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as "The Guardian of the Fields."

KYUREM.name: Kyurem
KYUREM.pokedex: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

KELDEO.name: Keldeo
KELDEO.pokedex: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.

MELOETTA.name: Meloetta
MELOETTA.pokedex: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

GENESECT.name: Genesect
GENESECT.pokedex: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

CHESPIN.name: Chespin
CHESPIN.pokedex: Such a thick shell of wood covers its head and back that even a direct hit from a truck wouldn't faze it.

QUILLADIN.name: Quilladin
QUILLADIN.pokedex: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won't start fights.

CHESNAUGHT.name: Chesnaught
CHESNAUGHT.pokedex: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.

FENNEKIN.name: Fennekin
FENNEKIN.pokedex: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.

BRAIXEN.name: Braixen
BRAIXEN.pokedex: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.

DELPHOX.name: Delphox
DELPHOX.pokedex: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.

FROAKIE.name: Froakie
FROAKIE.pokedex: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.

FROGADIER.name: Frogadier
FROGADIER.pokedex: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute's time.

GRENINJA.name: Greninja
GRENINJA.pokedex: It appears and vanishes with a ninja's grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

BUNNELBY.name: Bunnelby
BUNNELBY.pokedex: It has ears like shovels. Digging holes strengthens its ears so much that they can sever thick roots effortlessly.

DIGGERSBY.name: Diggersby
DIGGERSBY.pokedex: As powerful as an excavator, its ears can reduce dense bedrock to rubble. When it's finished digging, it lounges lazily.

FLETCHLING.name: Fletchling
FLETCHLING.pokedex: Despite the beauty of its lilting voice, it's merciless to intruders that enter its territory.

FLETCHINDER.name: Fletchinder
FLETCHINDER.pokedex: The hotter the flame sac on its belly, the faster it can fly, but it takes some time to get the fire going.

TALONFLAME.name: Talonflame
TALONFLAME.pokedex: When attacking prey, it can reach speeds of up to 310 mph. It finishes its prey off with a colossal kick.

SCATTERBUG.name: Scatterbug
SCATTERBUG.pokedex: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.

SPEWPA.name: Spewpa
SPEWPA.pokedex: The beaks of bird Pokémon can't begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.

VIVILLON.name: Vivillon
VIVILLON.pokedex: The patterns on this Pokémon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

LITLEO.name: Litleo
LITLEO.pokedex: They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokémon are quick to fight.

PYROAR.name: Pyroar
PYROAR.pokedex: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride's cubs.

FLABEBE.name: Flabébé
FLABEBE.pokedex: When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind's embrace with an untroubled heart.

FLOETTE.name: Floette
FLOETTE.pokedex: When the flowers of a well-tended flower bed bloom, it appears and celebrates with an elegant dance.

FLORGES.name: Florges
FLORGES.pokedex: In times long past, governors of castles would invite Florges to create flower gardens to embellish the castle domains.

SKIDDO.name: Skiddo
SKIDDO.pokedex: If it has sunshine and water, it doesn't need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.

GOGOAT.name: Gogoat
GOGOAT.pokedex: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.

PANCHAM.name: Pancham
PANCHAM.pokedex: It does its level best to glare and pull a scary face, but it can't help grinning if anyone pats its head.

PANGORO.name: Pangoro
PANGORO.pokedex: It charges ahead and bashes its opponents like a berserker, uncaring about any hits it might take. Its arms are mighty enough to snap a telephone pole.

FURFROU.name: Furfrou
FURFROU.pokedex: Historically, in the Kalos region, these Pokémon were the designated guardians of the king.

ESPURR.name: Espurr
ESPURR.pokedex: It has enough psychic energy to blast everything within 300 feet of itself, but it has no control over its power.

MEOWSTIC.name: Meowstic
MEOWSTIC.pokedex: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.

HONEDGE.name: Honedge
HONEDGE.pokedex: If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person's arm and drains that person's life energy completely.

DOUBLADE.name: Doublade
DOUBLADE.pokedex: The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.

AEGISLASH.name: Aegislash
AEGISLASH.pokedex: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.

SPRITZEE.name: Spritzee
SPRITZEE.pokedex: In the past, rather than using perfume, royal ladies carried a Spritzee that would waft a fragrance they liked.

AROMATISSE.name: Aromatisse
AROMATISSE.pokedex: Its scent is so overpowering that, unless a Trainer happens to really enjoy the smell, he or she will have a hard time walking alongside it.

SWIRLIX.name: Swirlix
SWIRLIX.pokedex: Because it eats nothing but sweets, its fur is as sticky sweet as cotton candy.

SLURPUFF.name: Slurpuff
SLURPUFF.pokedex: Its sense of smell is 100 million times better than a human's, so even the faintest scent tells it about everything in the area. It's like it can see with its nose!

INKAY.name: Inkay
INKAY.pokedex: It flashes the light-emitting spots on its body, which drains its opponent's will to fight. It takes the opportunity to scuttle away and hide.

MALAMAR.name: Malamar
MALAMAR.pokedex: It lures its prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.

BINACLE.name: Binacle
BINACLE.pokedex: They stretch and then contract, yanking their rocks along with them in bold hops. They eat seaweed that washes up on the shoreline.

BARBARACLE.name: Barbaracle
BARBARACLE.pokedex: Barbaracle's legs and hands have minds of their own, and they will move independently. But they usually follow the head's orders.

SKRELP.name: Skrelp
SKRELP.pokedex: It looks just like rotten kelp. It hides from foes while storing up power for its evolution.

DRAGALGE.name: Dragalge
DRAGALGE.pokedex: Tales are told of ships that wander into seas where Dragalge live, never to return.

CLAUNCHER.name: Clauncher
CLAUNCHER.pokedex: Through controlled explosions of internal gas, it can expel water like a pistol shot. At close distances, it can shatter rock.

CLAWITZER.name: Clawitzer
CLAWITZER.pokedex: By expelling water from the nozzle in the back of its claw, it can move at a speed of 60 knots.

HELIOPTILE.name: Helioptile
HELIOPTILE.pokedex: The frills on either side of its head have cells that generate electricity when exposed to sunlight.

HELIOLISK.name: Heliolisk
HELIOLISK.pokedex: It stimulates its muscles with electricity, boosting the strength in its legs and enabling it to run 100 yards in five seconds.

TYRUNT.name: Tyrunt
TYRUNT.pokedex: This is an ancient Pokémon, revived in modern times. It has a violent disposition, and it'll tear apart anything it gets between its hefty jaws.

TYRANTRUM.name: Tyrantrum
TYRANTRUM.pokedex: This Pokémon is from about 100,000,000 years ago. It has the presence of a king, vicious but magnificent.

AMAURA.name: Amaura
AMAURA.pokedex: This Pokémon was successfully restored from a fossil. In the past, it lived with others of its kind in cold lands where there were fewer predators.

AURORUS.name: Aurorus
AURORUS.pokedex: Aurorus was restored from a fossil. It's said that when this Pokémon howls, auroras appear in the night sky.

SYLVEON.name: Sylveon
SYLVEON.pokedex: Sylveon's ribbon-like feelers emit an aura that erases any sense of hostility, enabling it to stop fights. It wraps its feelers to its Trainer in order to read their feelings.

HAWLUCHA.name: Hawlucha
HAWLUCHA.pokedex: With its wings, it controls its position in the air. It likes to attack from above, a maneuver that is difficult to defend against.

DEDENNE.name: Dedenne
DEDENNE.pokedex: It uses its tail to absorb electricity from power plants or from outlets in houses, and then it fires the electricity from its whiskers.

CARBINK.name: Carbink
CARBINK.pokedex: It's said that somewhere in the world, there's a mineral vein housing a large pack of slumbering Carbink. It's also said that this pack has a queen.

GOOMY.name: Goomy
GOOMY.pokedex: It's covered in a slimy membrane that makes any punches or kicks slide off it harmlessly.

SLIGGOO.name: Sliggoo
SLIGGOO.pokedex: It's very friendly toward people. If you grow close to it, Goodra will hug you with its sticky, slime-covered body. Don't get mad.

GOODRA.name: Goodra
GOODRA.pokedex: It attacks with retractable horns. It throws a punch that's the equivalent of the force of a hundred pro boxers.

KLEFKI.name: Klefki
KLEFKI.pokedex: It never lets go of a key that it likes, so people give it the keys to vaults and safes as a way to prevent crime.

PHANTUMP.name: Phantump
PHANTUMP.pokedex: According to old tales, these Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died while lost in the forest.

TREVENANT.name: Trevenant
TREVENANT.pokedex: Using its roots as a nervous system, it controls the trees in the forest. It's kind to the Pokémon that reside in its body.

PUMPKABOO.name: Pumpkaboo
PUMPKABOO.pokedex: It is said to carry wandering spirits to the place where they belong so they can move on.

GOURGEIST.name: Gourgeist
GOURGEIST.pokedex: It enwraps its prey in its hairlike arms. It sings joyfully as it observes the suffering of its prey.

BERGMITE.name: Bergmite
BERGMITE.pokedex: Using air of -50 degrees Fahrenheit, they freeze opponents solid. They live in herds above the snow line on mountains.

AVALUGG.name: Avalugg
AVALUGG.pokedex: The way several Bergmite and Dreepy like to huddle on its back makes it look like an aircraft carrier made of ice.

NOIBAT.name: Noibat
NOIBAT.pokedex: Even a robust wrestler will become dizzy and unable to stand when exposed to its 200,000-hertz ultrasonic waves.

NOIVERN.name: Noivern
NOIVERN.pokedex: The ultrasonic waves it emits from its ears can reduce a large boulder to pebbles. It swoops out of the dark to attack.

XERNEAS.name: Xerneas
XERNEAS.pokedex: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.

YVELTAL.name: Yveltal
YVELTAL.pokedex: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

ZYGARDE.name: Zygarde
ZYGARDE.pokedex: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

DIANCIE.name: Diancie
DIANCIE.pokedex: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.

HOOPA.name: Hoopa
HOOPA.pokedex: It gathers things it likes and passes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.

VOLCANION.name: Volcanion
VOLCANION.pokedex: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

ROWLET.name: Rowlet
ROWLET.pokedex: It sends its feathers, which are as sharp as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong, so its kicks are also formidable.

DARTRIX.name: Dartrix
DARTRIX.pokedex: This narcissistic Pokémon is a clean freak. If you don't groom it diligently, it will stop listening to you.

DECIDUEYE.name: Decidueye
DECIDUEYE.pokedex: It nocks its arrow quills and shoots them at opponents. When it simply can't afford to miss, it tugs the vine on its head to improve its focus.

LITTEN.name: Litten
LITTEN.pokedex: If you try too hard to get close to it, it won't open up to you. Even if you do grow close, giving it too much affection is still a no-no.

TORRACAT.name: Torracat
TORRACAT.pokedex: It can act spoiled if it grows close to its Trainer. A powerful Pokémon, its sharp claws can leave its Trainer's whole body covered in scratches.

INCINEROAR.name: Incineroar
INCINEROAR.pokedex: Although it's rough mannered and egotistical, it finds beating down unworthy opponents boring. It gets motivated for stronger opponents.

POPPLIO.name: Popplio
POPPLIO.pokedex: The balloons it inflates with its nose grow larger and larger as it practices day by day.

BRIONNE.name: Brionne
BRIONNE.pokedex: It gets excited when it sees a dance it doesn't know. This hard worker practices diligently until it can learn that dance.

PRIMARINA.name: Primarina
PRIMARINA.pokedex: To Primarina, every battle is a stage. It takes down its prey with beautiful singing and dancing.

PIKIPEK.name: Pikipek
PIKIPEK.pokedex: It pecks at trees with its hard beak. You can get some idea of its mood or condition from the rhythm of its pecking.

TRUMBEAK.name: Trumbeak
TRUMBEAK.pokedex: It can bend the tip of its beak to produce over a hundred different cries at will.

TOUCANNON.name: Toucannon
TOUCANNON.pokedex: They smack beaks with others of their kind to communicate. The strength and number of hits tell each other how they feel.

YUNGOOS.name: Yungoos
YUNGOOS.pokedex: Its stomach takes up most of its long torso. It's a big eater, so the amount Trainers have to spend on its food is no laughing matter.

GUMSHOOS.name: Gumshoos
GUMSHOOS.pokedex: Although it wasn't originally found in Alola, this Pokémon was brought over a long time ago when there was a huge Rattata outbreak.

GRUBBIN.name: Grubbin
GRUBBIN.pokedex: If you find its nest, you shouldn't stick your hand inside. You'll get bitten by an irritated Grubbin.

CHARJABUG.name: Charjabug
CHARJABUG.pokedex: It buries itself in fallen leaves and barely moves, munching away on humus. If you accidentally step on one, you'll get a shock!

VIKAVOLT.name: Vikavolt
VIKAVOLT.pokedex: It has an organ that generates electricity in its abdomen. It concentrates energy in its jaws and fires off jolts of electricity.

CRABRAWLER.name: Crabrawler
CRABRAWLER.pokedex: Its hard pincers are well suited to both offense and defense. Fights between two Crabrawler are like boxing matches.

CRABOMINABLE.name: Crabominable
CRABOMINABLE.pokedex: It stores coldness in its pincers and pummels its foes. It can even smash thick walls of ice to bits!

ORICORIO.name: Oricorio
ORICORIO.pokedex: It wins the hearts of its enemies with its passionate dancing and then uses the opening it creates to burn them up with blazing flames.

CUTIEFLY.name: Cutiefly
CUTIEFLY.pokedex: Cutiefly is able to detect the aura of living things, which it uses to find flowers. Cutiefly tend to gather around beings feeling strong emotions.

RIBOMBEE.name: Ribombee
RIBOMBEE.pokedex: Ribombee hates rain as it turns its hair dirty and its pollen damp. When storms are on the horizon, Ribombee hides in tree hollows waiting for it to pass.

ROCKRUFF.name: Rockruff
ROCKRUFF.pokedex: As they develop, their disposition grows more violent and aggressive. Many Trainers find them too much to handle and abandon them.

LYCANROC.name: Lycanroc
LYCANROC.pokedex: The sharp rocks in its mane can cut like knives. Lycanroc wears its prey down by degrees before finishing them off.

WISHIWASHI.name: Wishiwashi
WISHIWASHI.pokedex: They're weak, so they move in schools. However, they can also often be seen all alone, having strayed from the school.

MAREANIE.name: Mareanie
MAREANIE.pokedex: They eat Corsola branches, so Mareanie are hated by craftsmen who work with Corsola branches that have naturally fallen off.

TOXAPEX.name: Toxapex
TOXAPEX.pokedex: To attack, this Pokémon sends toxic spikes flying at its enemies. Ones that come close get mown down by the claws on its feet.

MUDBRAY.name: Mudbray
MUDBRAY.pokedex: It loves playing in the mud. If it isn't showered with mud on a daily basis, it gets stressed out and stops listening to its Trainer.

MUDSDALE.name: Mudsdale
MUDSDALE.pokedex: It remains calm and unmoving no matter the situation. It mixes dirt with the saliva in its mouth to make a special kind of mud.

DEWPIDER.name: Dewpider
DEWPIDER.pokedex: When two Dewpider meet, they display their water bubbles to each other. Then the one with the smaller bubble gets out of the other's way.

ARAQUANID.name: Araquanid
ARAQUANID.pokedex: It usually passes its time in the water. When its belly is full, it stores its subdued prey in the water bubble on its head.

FOMANTIS.name: Fomantis
FOMANTIS.pokedex: When the sun rises, Fomantis spreads its four leaves and bathes in the sunlight. The tip of its head has a pleasant aroma.

LURANTIS.name: Lurantis
LURANTIS.pokedex: For self-protection, it pretends to be a bug Pokémon. Both of its arms bear keen-edged petals.

MORELULL.name: Morelull
MORELULL.pokedex: It scatters its shining spores around itself. Even though they're dangerous, nighttime tours of forests where Morelull live are popular.

SHIINOTIC.name: Shiinotic
SHIINOTIC.pokedex: It puts its prey to sleep and siphons off their vitality through the tip of its arms. If one of its kind is weakened, it helps by sending it vitality.

SALANDIT.name: Salandit
SALANDIT.pokedex: The males will do whatever the females tell them. They give the females most of their food.

SALAZZLE.name: Salazzle
SALAZZLE.pokedex: Salazzle lives deep in caves and forces the Salandit it has attracted with its pheromones to serve it.

STUFFUL.name: Stufful
STUFFUL.pokedex: It boasts power enough to split large trees in half. The organ on its rear releases an odor that it uses to communicate with others of its kind.

BEWEAR.name: Bewear
BEWEAR.pokedex: It waves its hands wildly in intimidation and warning. Life is over for anyone who doesn't run away as fast as possible.

BOUNSWEET.name: Bounsweet
BOUNSWEET.pokedex: Because of its sweet, delicious aroma, bird Pokémon are always after it, but it's not intelligent enough to care.

STEENEE.name: Steenee
STEENEE.pokedex: It's protected by its hard sepals, so it plays with bird Pokémon without worry. They peck it relentlessly, but it doesn't care.

TSAREENA.name: Tsareena
TSAREENA.pokedex: A master of grand and beautiful kicks, it can knock out even kickboxing champions with a single blow.

COMFEY.name: Comfey
COMFEY.pokedex: It stretches sticky vines out from its head and picks flowers to adorn itself with. When it doesn't have any flowers, it feels uneasy.

ORANGURU.name: Oranguru
ORANGURU.pokedex: It normally spends its time meditating in the treetops. It throws Poké Balls and gives other Pokémon orders as it pleases.

PASSIMIAN.name: Passimian
PASSIMIAN.pokedex: They use their saliva to stick leaves to their shoulders. You can tell what troop they belong to from the position of the leaves.

WIMPOD.name: Wimpod
WIMPOD.pokedex: It will pick up anything it finds on the ground. Sometimes it finds coins, so Murkrow and Meowth will go after it.

GOLISOPOD.name: Golisopod
GOLISOPOD.pokedex: The shell covering its body is as hard as diamond. This Pokémon will do anything it takes to win.

SANDYGAST.name: Sandygast
SANDYGAST.pokedex: It likes the shovel on its head, so Sandygast will get serious and fight any children who come to take it back.

PALOSSAND.name: Palossand
PALOSSAND.pokedex: Each of its grains of sand has its own will. Palossand eats small Pokémon and siphons away their vital essence while they're still alive.

PYUKUMUKU.name: Pyukumuku
PYUKUMUKU.pokedex: The tradition known as Pyukumuku chucking started from the custom of throwing Pyukumuku back into the sea after they wash onshore.

TYPENULL.name: Type: Null
TYPENULL.pokedex: A Pokémon weapon developed for a specific mission, it went berserk during an experiment, so it was cryogenically frozen.

SILVALLY.name: Silvally
SILVALLY.pokedex: This is its form once it has awakened and evolved. Freed from its heavy mask, its speed is greatly increased.

MINIOR.name: Minior
MINIOR.pokedex: It lives in the ozone layer, where it becomes food for stronger Pokémon. When it tries to run away, it falls to the ground.

KOMALA.name: Komala
KOMALA.pokedex: It stays asleep from the moment it's born. When it falls into a deep sleep, it stops moving altogether.

TURTONATOR.name: Turtonator
TURTONATOR.pokedex: It lives in volcanoes and eats sulfur and other minerals. Materials from the food it eats form the basis of its explosive shell.

TOGEDEMARU.name: Togedemaru
TOGEDEMARU.pokedex: When it's surprised or agitated, the 14 fur spikes on its back will stand up involuntarily.

MIMIKYU.name: Mimikyu
MIMIKYU.pokedex: Although it's a quiet, lonely Pokémon, if you try to look at what's under its rag, it will become agitated and resist violently.

BRUXISH.name: Bruxish
BRUXISH.pokedex: It burrows beneath the sand, radiating psychic power from the protuberance on its head. It waits for prey as it surveys the area.

DRAMPA.name: Drampa
DRAMPA.pokedex: If a child it has made friends with is bullied, Drampa will find the bully's house and burn it to the ground.

DHELMISE.name: Dhelmise
DHELMISE.pokedex: It wraps its prey in green seaweed and sucks away their vitality. It only likes to go after big prey like Wailord.

JANGMOO.name: Jangmo-o
JANGMOO.pokedex: It smacks the scales on its head against rocks or against the ground to frighten its opponents. It can also contact its friends with these noises.

HAKAMOO.name: Hakamo-o
HAKAMOO.pokedex: It makes noise by clanging its scales together. When the rhythm has reached its peak, Hakamo-o attacks.

KOMMOO.name: Kommo-o
KOMMOO.pokedex: When it howls after finishing off its prey, the metallic sounds of its celebrating comrades can be heard from all around.

TAPUKOKO.name: Tapu Koko
TAPUKOKO.pokedex: Although it's called a guardian deity, if a person or Pokémon puts it in a bad mood, it will become a malevolent deity and attack.

TAPULELE.name: Tapu Lele
TAPULELE.pokedex: It heals the wounds of people and Pokémon by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales. This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.

TAPUBULU.name: Tapu Bulu
TAPUBULU.pokedex: Although it's called a guardian deity, it's violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.

TAPUFINI.name: Tapu Fini
TAPUFINI.pokedex: This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog, it came to be both feared and revered.

COSMOG.name: Cosmog
COSMOG.pokedex: Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown away by the slightest breeze, it doesn't seem to care.

COSMOEM.name: Cosmoem
COSMOEM.pokedex: The king who ruled Alola in times of antiquity called it the "cocoon of the stars" and built an altar to worship it.

SOLGALEO.name: Solgaleo
SOLGALEO.pokedex: Sometimes the result of its opening an Ultra Wormhole is that energy and life-forms from other worlds are called here to this world.

LUNALA.name: Lunala
LUNALA.pokedex: Records of it exist in writings from long, long ago, where it was known by the name "the beast that calls the moon."

NIHILEGO.name: Nihilego
NIHILEGO.pokedex: A life-form from another world, it was dubbed a UB and is thought to produce a strong neurotoxin.

BUZZWOLE.name: Buzzwole
BUZZWOLE.pokedex: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

PHEROMOSA.name: Pheromosa
PHEROMOSA.pokedex: A life-form that lives in another world, its body is thin and supple, but it also possesses great power.

XURKITREE.name: Xurkitree
XURKITREE.pokedex: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

CELESTEELA.name: Celesteela
CELESTEELA.pokedex: One of the dangerous UBs, high energy readings can be detected coming from both of its huge arms.

KARTANA.name: Kartana
KARTANA.pokedex: This Ultra Beast's body, which is as thin as paper, is like a sharpened sword.

GUZZLORD.name: Guzzlord
GUZZLORD.pokedex: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

NECROZMA.name: Necrozma
NECROZMA.pokedex: It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light, which serves as its energy. It's apparently from another world.

MAGEARNA.name: Magearna
MAGEARNA.pokedex: It synchronizes its consciousness with others to understand their feelings. This faculty makes it useful for taking care of people.

MARSHADOW.name: Marshadow
MARSHADOW.pokedex: It slips into the shadows of others and mimics their powers and movements. As it improves, it becomes stronger than those it's imitating.

POIPOLE.name: Poipole
POIPOLE.pokedex: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.

NAGANADEL.name: Naganadel
NAGANADEL.pokedex: It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid inside its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.

STAKATAKA.name: Stakataka
STAKATAKA.pokedex: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.

BLACEPHALON.name: Blacephalon
BLACEPHALON.pokedex: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It's apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

ZERAORA.name: Zeraora
ZERAORA.pokedex: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they'll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.

MELTAN.name: Meltan
MELTAN.pokedex: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

MELMETAL.name: Melmetal
MELMETAL.pokedex: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.

GROOKEY.name: Grookey
GROOKEY.pokedex: It attacks with rapid beats of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed, it gets more and more pumped.

THWACKEY.name: Thwackey
THWACKEY.pokedex: When it's drumming out rapid beats in battle, it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won't even notice that it's already knocked out its opponent.

RILLABOOM.name: Rillaboom
RILLABOOM.pokedex: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

SCORBUNNY.name: Scorbunny
SCORBUNNY.pokedex: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it's raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.

RABOOT.name: Raboot
RABOOT.pokedex: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.

CINDERACE.name: Cinderace
CINDERACE.pokedex: It's skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.

SOBBLE.name: Sobble
SOBBLE.pokedex: When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokémon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.

DRIZZILE.name: Drizzile
DRIZZILE.pokedex: Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.

INTELEON.name: Inteleon
INTELEON.pokedex: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes' weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.

SKWOVET.name: Skwovet
SKWOVET.pokedex: It eats berries nonstop, a habit that has made it more resilient than it looks. It'll show up on farms, searching for yet more berries.

GREEDENT.name: Greedent
GREEDENT.pokedex: Common throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon has strong teeth and can chew through the toughest of berry shells.

ROOKIDEE.name: Rookidee
ROOKIDEE.pokedex: Jumping nimbly about, this small-bodied Pokémon takes advantage of even the slightest opportunity to disorient larger opponents.

CORVISQUIRE.name: Corvisquire
CORVISQUIRE.pokedex: The lessons of many harsh battles have taught it how to accurately judge an opponent's strength.

CORVIKNIGHT.name: Corviknight
CORVIKNIGHT.pokedex: With their great intellect and flying skills, these Pokémon very successfully act as the Galar region's airborne taxi service.

BLIPBUG.name: Blipbug
BLIPBUG.pokedex: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

DOTTLER.name: Dottler
DOTTLER.pokedex: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

ORBEETLE.name: Orbeetle
ORBEETLE.pokedex: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what's around it, and what's around it can include things over six miles away.

NICKIT.name: Nickit
NICKIT.pokedex: Cunning and cautious, this Pokémon survives by stealing food from others. It erases its tracks with swipes of its tail as it makes off with its plunder.

THIEVUL.name: Thievul
THIEVUL.pokedex: With a lithe body and sharp claws, it goes around stealing food and eggs. Boltund is its natural enemy.

GOSSIFLEUR.name: Gossifleur
GOSSIFLEUR.pokedex: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.

ELDEGOSS.name: Eldegoss
ELDEGOSS.pokedex: The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn, a Galar regional specialty.

WOOLOO.name: Wooloo
WOOLOO.pokedex: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won't be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.

DUBWOOL.name: Dubwool
DUBWOOL.pokedex: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.

CHEWTLE.name: Chewtle
CHEWTLE.pokedex: It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokémon bites down and never lets go.

DREDNAW.name: Drednaw
DREDNAW.pokedex: This Pokémon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.

YAMPER.name: Yamper
YAMPER.pokedex: This gluttonous Pokémon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.

BOLTUND.name: Boltund
BOLTUND.pokedex: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.

ROLYCOLY.name: Rolycoly
ROLYCOLY.pokedex: It can race around like a unicycle, even on rough, rocky terrain. Burning coal sustains it.

CARKOL.name: Carkol
CARKOL.pokedex: By rapidly rolling its legs, it can travel at over 18 mph. The temperature of the flames it breathes exceeds 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

COALOSSAL.name: Coalossal
COALOSSAL.pokedex: While it's engaged in battle, its mountain of coal will burn bright red, sending off sparks that scorch the surrounding area.

APPLIN.name: Applin
APPLIN.pokedex: As soon as it's born, it burrows into an apple. The apple serves as both a food source and a home.

FLAPPLE.name: Flapple
FLAPPLE.pokedex: It flies on wings of apple skin and spits a powerful acid. It can also change its shape into that of an apple.

APPLETUN.name: Appletun
APPLETUN.pokedex: A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokémon it preys on. The skin on its back is especially yummy.

SILICOBRA.name: Silicobra
SILICOBRA.pokedex: It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded, it burrows into the ground to hide.

SANDACONDA.name: Sandaconda
SANDACONDA.pokedex: Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.

CRAMORANT.name: Cramorant
CRAMORANT.pokedex: This hungry Pokémon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokémon other than its preferred prey.

ARROKUDA.name: Arrokuda
ARROKUDA.pokedex: After it's eaten its fill, its movements become extremely sluggish. That's when Cramorant swallows it up.

BARRASKEWDA.name: Barraskewda
BARRASKEWDA.pokedex: It spins its tail fins to propel itself, surging forward at speeds of over 100 knots before ramming prey and spearing into them.

TOXEL.name: Toxel
TOXEL.pokedex: It manipulates the chemical makeup of its poison to produce electricity. The voltage is weak, but it can cause a tingling paralysis.

TOXTRICITY.name: Toxtricity
TOXTRICITY.pokedex: This short-tempered and aggressive Pokémon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.

SIZZLIPEDE.name: Sizzlipede
SIZZLIPEDE.pokedex: It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they're well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.

CENTISKORCH.name: Centiskorch
CENTISKORCH.pokedex: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.

CLOBBOPUS.name: Clobbopus
CLOBBOPUS.pokedex: Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn't alarmed when that happens, it knows they'll grow back. It's about as smart as a three-year-old.

GRAPPLOCT.name: Grapploct
GRAPPLOCT.pokedex: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.

SINISTEA.name: Sinistea
SINISTEA.pokedex: The teacup in which this Pokémon makes its home is a famous piece of antique tableware. Many forgeries are in circulation.

POLTEAGEIST.name: Polteageist
POLTEAGEIST.pokedex: Leaving leftover black tea unattended is asking for this Pokémon to come along and pour itself into it, turning the tea into a new Polteageist.

HATENNA.name: Hatenna
HATENNA.pokedex: If this Pokémon senses a strong emotion, it will run away as fast as it can. It prefers areas without people.

HATTREM.name: Hattrem
HATTREM.pokedex: Using the braids on its head, it pummels foes to get them to quiet down. One blow from those braids would knock out a professional boxer.

HATTERENE.name: Hatterene
HATTERENE.pokedex: If you're too loud around it, you risk being torn apart by the claws on its tentacle. This Pokémon is also known as the Forest Witch.

IMPIDIMP.name: Impidimp
IMPIDIMP.pokedex: It sneaks into people's homes, stealing things and feasting on the negative energy of the frustrated occupants.

MORGREM.name: Morgrem
MORGREM.pokedex: With sly cunning, it tries to lure people into the woods. Some believe it to have the power to make crops grow.

GRIMMSNARL.name: Grimmsnarl
GRIMMSNARL.pokedex: Its hairs work like muscle fibers. When its hairs unfurl, they latch on to opponents, ensnaring them as tentacles would.

OBSTAGOON.name: Obstagoon
OBSTAGOON.pokedex: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.

PERRSERKER.name: Perrserker
PERRSERKER.pokedex: After many battles, it evolved dangerous claws that come together to form daggers when extended.

CURSOLA.name: Cursola
CURSOLA.pokedex: Be cautious of the ectoplasmic body surrounding its soul. You'll become stiff as stone if you touch it.

SIRFETCHD.name: Sirfetch'd
SIRFETCHD.pokedex: After deflecting attacks with its hard leaf shield, it strikes back with its sharp leek stalk. The leek stalk is both weapon and food.

MRRIME.name: Mr. Rime
MRRIME.pokedex: Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.

RUNERIGUS.name: Runerigus
RUNERIGUS.pokedex: Never touch its shadowlike body, or you'll be shown the horrific memories behind the picture carved into it.

MILCERY.name: Milcery
MILCERY.pokedex: They say that any patisserie visited by Milcery is guaranteed success and good fortune.

ALCREMIE.name: Alcremie
ALCREMIE.pokedex: When Alcremie is content, the cream it secretes from its hands becomes sweeter and richer.

FALINKS.name: Falinks
FALINKS.pokedex: The six of them work together as one Pokémon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.

PINCURCHIN.name: Pincurchin
PINCURCHIN.pokedex: It stores electricity in each spine. Even if one gets broken off, it still continues to emit electricity for at least three hours.

SNOM.name: Snom
SNOM.pokedex: It eats snow that piles up on the ground. The more snow it eats, the bigger and more impressive the spikes on its back grow.

FROSMOTH.name: Frosmoth
FROSMOTH.pokedex: It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.

STONJOURNER.name: Stonjourner
STONJOURNER.pokedex: Once a year, on a specific date and at a specific time, they gather out of nowhere and form up in a circle.

EISCUE.name: Eiscue
EISCUE.pokedex: This Pokémon keeps its heat-sensitive head cool with ice. It fishes for its food, dangling its single hair into the sea to lure in prey.

INDEEDEE.name: Indeedee
INDEEDEE.pokedex: Through its horns, it can pick up on the emotions of creatures around it. Positive emotions are the source of its strength.

MORPEKO.name: Morpeko
MORPEKO.pokedex: It carries electrically roasted seeds with it as if they're precious treasures. No matter how much it eats, it always gets hungry again in short order.

CUFANT.name: Cufant
CUFANT.pokedex: If a job requires serious strength, this Pokémon will excel at it. Its copper body tarnishes in the rain, turning a vibrant green color.

COPPERAJAH.name: Copperajah
COPPERAJAH.pokedex: These Pokémon live in herds. Their trunks have incredible grip strength, strong enough to crush giant rocks into powder.

DRACOZOLT.name: Dracozolt
DRACOZOLT.pokedex: The powerful muscles in its tail generate its electricity. Compared to its lower body, its upper half is entirely too small.

ARCTOZOLT.name: Arctozolt
ARCTOZOLT.pokedex: This Pokémon lived on prehistoric seashores and was able to preserve food with the ice on its body. It went extinct because it moved so slowly.

DRACOVISH.name: Dracovish
DRACOVISH.pokedex: Its mighty legs are capable of running at speeds exceeding 40 mph, but this Pokémon can't breathe unless it's underwater.

ARCTOVISH.name: Arctovish
ARCTOVISH.pokedex: The skin on its face is impervious to attack, but breathing difficulties made this Pokémon go extinct anyway.

DURALUDON.name: Duraludon
DURALUDON.pokedex: The special metal that composes its body is very light, so this Pokémon has considerable agility. It lives in caves because it dislikes the rain.

DREEPY.name: Dreepy
DREEPY.pokedex: If this weak Pokémon is by itself, a mere child could defeat it. But if Dreepy has friends to help it train, it can evolve and become much stronger.

DRAKLOAK.name: Drakloak
DRAKLOAK.pokedex: Without a Dreepy to place on its head and care for, it gets so uneasy it'll try to substitute any Pokémon it finds for the missing Dreepy.

DRAGAPULT.name: Dragapult
DRAGAPULT.pokedex: Apparently the Dreepy inside Dragapult's horns eagerly look forward to being launched out at Mach speeds.

ZACIAN.name: Zacian
ZACIAN.pokedex: This Pokémon has slumbered for many years. Some say it's Zamazenta's elder sister, others say the two Pokémon are rivals.

ZAMAZENTA.name: Zamazenta
ZAMAZENTA.pokedex: This Pokémon slept for aeons while in the form of a statue. It was asleep for so long, people forgot that it ever existed.

ETERNATUS.name: Eternatus
ETERNATUS.pokedex: It was inside a meteorite that fell 20,000 years ago. There seems to be a connection between this Pokémon and the Dynamax phenomenon.

KUBFU.name: Kubfu
KUBFU.pokedex: If Kubfu pulls the long white hair on its head, its fighting spirit heightens and power wells up from the depths of its belly.

URSHIFU.name: Urshifu
URSHIFU.pokedex: Inhabiting the mountains of a distant region, this Pokémon races across sheer cliffs, training its legs and refining its moves.

ZARUDE.name: Zarude
ZARUDE.pokedex: Once the vines on Zarude's body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.

REGIELEKI.name: Regieleki
REGIELEKI.pokedex: The fifth of the titans, built to commemorate an era of electricity. It is as inscrutable as a cutting-edge supercomputer.

REGIDRAGO.name: Regidrago
REGIDRAGO.pokedex: The first of the titans, built to commemorate an era when dragons ruled. It is as terrifying as an apex predator.

GLASTRIER.name: Glastrier
GLASTRIER.pokedex: Glastrier has tremendous physical strength, and the mask of ice covering its face is 100 times harder than diamond.

SPECTRIER.name: Spectrier
SPECTRIER.pokedex: As it dashes through the night, Spectrier absorbs the life-force of sleeping creatures. It craves silence and solitude.

CALYREX.name: Calyrex
CALYREX.pokedex: Legend says that by using its power to see all events from past to future, this Pokémon saved the creatures of a forest from a meteorite strike.

WORNET.name: Wornet
WORNET.pokedex: Its final evolution has sent its killer instinct into overdrive. It obeys its trainer unfailingly, but will grow impatient without a good fight.

PAPELLUMEN.name: Papellumen
PAPELLUMEN.pokedex: Evolutionary power has supercharged its wings and their toxic scales, which turn to pure energy at the slightest provocation.

TEAMUJIN.name: Teamujin
TEAMUJIN.pokedex: Mother and daughter fight alongside each other, delivering blows in quick succession. Their battle bond is unbreakable.

HOUNDOMINUS.name: Houndominus
HOUNDOMINUS.pokedex: They are the steeds of the Elite Four of the Apocalypse, and their howls will ring in the end of days... or so the stories go.

RUBARIOR.name: Rubarior
RUBARIOR.pokedex: Attackers find their weaknesses and regrets reflected in the jewel Rubarior carries. If it feels unloved, it will make its Trainer cry.

DECEAT.name: Deceat
DECEAT.pokedex: Fans argue whether it's the cutest terrifying Pokémon or the creepiest cute Pokémon. It will act cute or scary depending on its trainer's whims.

PALMANTRA.name: Palmantra
PALMANTRA.pokedex: This Pokémon can go up to four years without eating a single meal. Through intense training, it is able to fight in a manner indistinguishable from a dance.

MANERGETIC.name: Manergetic
MANERGETIC.pokedex: If not calmed during storms, it will cause havoc by trying to race lightning bolts.

SCARODON.name: Scarodon
SCARODON.pokedex: Its propulsion system is the basis for many ramjet engine designs. It eats four times its body weight in food before a battle and will still be hungry by the end.

DROMERUPT.name: Dromerupt
DROMERUPT.pokedex: Magma builds up in its body over time. If this Pokémon does not regularly erupt, it might accidentally destroy the area around it.

HYMNUS.name: Hymnus
HYMNUS.pokedex: This Pokémon's singing can bring even the most stoic Trainers to tears. Those who fall asleep on it are said to experience beautiful dreams.

MANIKLAW.name: Maniklaw
MANIKLAW.pokedex: Its pink claws and feet appear to be made of flesh, but are actually raw negative energy. When it is finally fully unzipped, it moves on to its next life.

ABSOLUS.name: Absolus
ABSOLUS.pokedex: It's loved for its elegantly intimidating looks. It may herald a coming cataclysm, but nothing gets between a trainer and a fashionable Pokémon.

HAEROBIC.name: Haerobic
HAEROBIC.pokedex: It patterns its fur and attacks after human fighters it looks up to. Only the most over-the-top action movies can inspire it to reach its true potential.

CONIFEAR.name: Conifear
CONIFEAR.pokedex: Blizzards follow it wherever it goes. It's often used as shelter by unsuspecting mountaineers, though it doesn't mind.

SENSIBELLE.name: Sensibelle
SENSIBELLE.pokedex: They are brought into hospitals when conventional medicine fails. They can hear the number of heartbeats a person has left, but will never tell.

SAHARICANE.name: Saharicane
SAHARICANE.pokedex: Its rough belly scales can pulverize entire quarries for sand to use in battle. Its fights with Flygon in the center of desert storms are the stuff of legend.

KLAWSAR.name: Klawsar
KLAWSAR.pokedex: Its claw has become so large that if it finds itself unable to clamp its opponent, it will just smack them with the blunt side.

SEISMAW.name: Seismaw
SEISMAW.pokedex: It balances itself like a sumo wrestler, making it nearly impossible to topple. Its squishy flesh is even more resilent than its shell.

ARCLAMOR.name: Arclamor
ARCLAMOR.pokedex: It subconsciously broadcasts the audio of its battles over radio waves. Tuning in at the right time will let you hear the performance of a lifetime.

BLASFEMMIE.name: Blasfemmie
BLASFEMMIE.pokedex: So tall it seems to defy the heavens, it lords its elevated position over other Pokémon. It grants its Trainer knowledge of sweet and sour.

SCARAPACE.name: Scarapace
SCARAPACE.pokedex: When the buzz of its wings becomes a roar, it's about to bolt at full speed. It isn't uncommon for its charges to send opponents through buildings.

ATLACROSS.name: Atlacross
ATLACROSS.pokedex: They can be seen watching the sky, trying to find a place to stand for when they inevitably attempt to deadlift the world.

SAURENAID.name: Saurenaid
SAURENAID.pokedex: The musical staff around its body is made of ice particles. The symbols are indecipherable, but some say they've heard Saurenaid speak its own language.

DONSTER.name: Donster
DONSTER.pokedex: It's unclear what the objects embedded in its body are or where they came from. More must be added over time, though, as anything it absorbs is quickly dissolved.

NIBELONG.name: Nibelong
NIBELONG.pokedex: Scientists are divided as to whether its incredible length inspired internet memes, or whether seeing memes caused a Meowth to undergo unprecedented evolution.

GIGANTEON.name: Giganteon
GIGANTEON.pokedex: Its fluffiness, friendliness, and massive size make it beloved by nearly everyone. Attackers don't know where to begin.

GIGACHU.name: Gigachu
GIGACHU.pokedex: Rarely, a Pikachu grows to incredible size instead of evolving into Raichu. It can power settlements so long as it's fed properly.

MILLIBLAZE.name: Milliblaze
MILLIBLAZE.pokedex: Even solid titanium will melt in its coils. It uses the massive mirage it creates to confuse Volcarona in their frequent contests.

RIOJIN.name: Riojin
RIOJIN.pokedex: It fights in a state of complete clarity without mercy, fear, or stress. When it has achieved all its goals, it will simply cease to be.

TITANIX.name: Titanix
TITANIX.pokedex: Its crystalline parts resist all attempts to identify them. Titanix's gravitational abilities make some scientists speculate the crystals are neutron matter.

DIGNIPHITE.name: Digniphite
DIGNIPHITE.pokedex: After evolution, it has taken on the appearance of a great monument. If revered, it will protect nearby villages from all manner of disaster.

TOWERPODA.name: Towerpoda
TOWERPODA.pokedex: Nostalgic for the cavern home it has outgrown, it will weep molten glass. Those without trainers may find company serving as rookeries for bird Pokémon.

PTEROFLYTE.name: Pteroflyte
PTEROFLYTE.pokedex: In ancient times, this Pokémon was an apex predator. It has the strength to fly with a Tyrantrum in its claws.

REAVOR.name: Reavor
REAVOR.pokedex: Only exceptionally aggressive or well-trained Pokémon will willingly engage one in combat. Its ripping pincers threaten to turn foes to shrapnel.

GRIMICE.name: Grimice
GRIMICE.pokedex: It only closes its mouth to bite its foes, forcing its trainers to learn to interpret its emotions via its changes in eye shape, ear direction, and body temperature.

ARATTATA.name: A. Rattata
ARATTATA.pokedex: It shows no interest in anything that isn't fresh. If you take it shopping with you, it will help you pick out ingredients.

ARATICATE.name: A. Raticate
ARATICATE.pokedex: It makes its Rattata underlings gather food for it, dining solely on the most nutritious and delicious fare.

ARAICHU.name: A. Raichu
ARAICHU.pokedex: It can loose 100,000-volt bursts of electricity, instantly downing foes several times its size.

ASANDSHREW.name: A. Sandshrew
ASANDSHREW.pokedex: Life on mountains covered with deep snow has granted this Pokémon a body of ice that's as hard as steel.

ASANDSLASH.name: A. Sandslash
ASANDSLASH.pokedex: It lives in snowy mountains on southern islands. When a blizzard rolls in, this Pokémon hunkers down in the snow to avoid getting blown away.

AVULPIX.name: A. Vulpix
AVULPIX.pokedex: In hot weather, this Pokémon makes ice shards with its six tails and sprays them around to cool itself off.

ANINETALES.name: A. Ninetales
ANINETALES.pokedex: It lives on mountains perpetually covered in snow and is revered as a deity incarnate. It appears draped in a blizzard.

ADIGLETT.name: A. Diglett
ADIGLETT.pokedex: Its head sports an altered form of whiskers made of metal. When in communication with its comrades, its whiskers wobble to and fro.

ADUGTRIO.name: A. Dugtrio
ADUGTRIO.pokedex: Its shining gold hair provides it with protection. It's reputed that keeping any of its fallen hairs will bring bad luck.

AMEOWTH.name: A. Meowth
AMEOWTH.pokedex: It's impulsive, selfish, and fickle. It's very popular with some Trainers who like giving it the attention it needs.

GMEOWTH.name: G. Meowth
GMEOWTH.pokedex: These daring Pokémon have coins on their foreheads. Darker coins are harder, and harder coins garner more respect among Meowth.

APERSIAN.name: A. Persian
APERSIAN.pokedex: Its round face is a symbol of wealth. Persian that have bigger, plumper faces are considered more beautiful.

AGEODUDE.name: A. Geodude
AGEODUDE.pokedex: Geodude compete against each other with headbutts. The iron sand on their heads will stick to whichever one has stronger magnetism.

AGRAVELER.name: A. Graveler
AGRAVELER.pokedex: They eat rocks and often get into a scrap over them. The shock of Graveler smashing together causes a flash of light and a booming noise.

AGOLEM.name: A. Golem
AGOLEM.pokedex: It fires rocks charged with electricity. Even if the rock isn't fired that accurately, just grazing an opponent will cause numbness and fainting.

GPONYTA.name: G. Ponyta
GPONYTA.pokedex: This Pokémon will look into your eyes and read the contents of your heart. If it finds evil there, it promptly hides away.

GRAPIDASH.name: G. Rapidash
GRAPIDASH.pokedex: Brave and prideful, this Pokémon dashes airily through the forest, its steps aided by the psychic power stored in the fur on its fetlocks.

GSLOWPOKE.name: G. Slowpoke
GSLOWPOKE.pokedex: Because Galarian Slowpoke eat the seeds of a plant that grows only in Galar, their tails have developed a spicy flavor.

GSLOWBRO.name: G. Slowbro
GSLOWBRO.pokedex: If this Pokémon squeezes the tongue of the Shellder biting it, the Shellder will launch a toxic liquid from the tip of its shell.

GFARFETCHD.name: G. Farfetch'd
GFARFETCHD.pokedex: The stalks of leeks are thicker and longer in the Galar region. Farfetch'd that adapted to these stalks took on a unique form.

AGRIMER.name: A. Grimer
AGRIMER.pokedex: A Grimer, which had been brought in to solve a problem with garbage, developed over time into this form.

AMUK.name: A. Muk
AMUK.pokedex: The garbage it eats causes continuous chemical changes in its body, which produce its exceedingly vivid coloration.

AEXEGGUTOR.name: A. Exeggutor
AEXEGGUTOR.pokedex: As it grew taller and taller, it outgrew its reliance on psychic powers, while within it awakened the power of the sleeping dragon.

AMAROWAK.name: A. Marowak
AMAROWAK.pokedex: Its custom is to mourn its lost companions. Mounds of dirt by the side of the road mark the graves of the Marowak

GWEEZING.name: G. Weezing
GWEEZING.pokedex: Long ago, during a time when droves of factories fouled the air with pollution, Weezing changed into this form for some reason.

GMRMIME.name: G. Mr. Mime
GMRMIME.pokedex: It can radiate chilliness from the bottoms of its feet. It'll spend the whole day tap-dancing on a frozen floor.

GARTICUNO.name: G. Articuno
GARTICUNO.pokedex: Its feather-like blades are composed of psychic energy and can shear through thick iron sheets as if they were paper.

GZAPDOS.name: G. Zapdos
GZAPDOS.pokedex: One kick from its powerful legs will pulverize a dump truck. Supposedly, this Pokémon runs through the mountains at over 180 mph.

GMOLTRES.name: G. Moltres
GMOLTRES.pokedex: This Pokémon's sinister, flame-like aura will consume the spirit of any creature it hits. Victims become burned-out shadows of themselves.

GSLOWKING.name: G. Slowking
GSLOWKING.pokedex: Slowking can solve any problem present to it, but no one can understand a thing Slowking says.

GCORSOLA.name: G. Corsola
GCORSOLA.pokedex: Sudden climate change wiped out this ancient kind of Corsola. This Pokémon absorbs others' life-force through its branches.

GZIGZAGOON.name: G. Zigzagoon
GZIGZAGOON.pokedex: Thought to be the oldest form of Zigzagoon, it moves in zigzags and wreaks havoc upon its surroundings.

GLINOONE.name: G. Linoone
GLINOONE.pokedex: This very aggressive Pokémon will recklessly challenge opponents stronger than itself.

GDARUMAKA.name: G. Darumaka
GDARUMAKA.pokedex: The colder they get, the more energetic they are. They freeze their breath to make snowballs, using them as ammo for playful snowball fights.

GDARMANITAN.name: G. Darmanitan
GDARMANITAN.pokedex: Though it has a gentle disposition, it's also very strong. It will quickly freeze the snowball on its head before going for a headbutt.

GYAMASK.name: G. Yamask
GYAMASK.pokedex: It's said that this Pokémon was formed when an ancient clay tablet was drawn to a vengeful spirit.

GSTUNFISK.name: G. Stunfisk
GSTUNFISK.pokedex: Its conspicuous lips lure prey in as it lies in wait in the mud. When prey gets close, Stunfisk clamps its jagged steel fins down on them.

WYRDEER.name: Wyrdeer
WYRDEER.pokedex: The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokémon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well.

URSALUNA.name: Ursaluna
URSALUNA.pokedex: It is believed that the swampy terrain of its ancient home region gave Ursaluna its burly physique and capacity to manipulate peat at will.

KLEAVOR.name: Kleavor
KLEAVOR.pokedex: A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone.

BASCULEGION.name: Basculegion
BASCULEGION.pokedex: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream.

HTYPHLOSION.name: H. Typhlosion
HTYPHLOSION.pokedex: Said to purify lost, forsaken souls with its flames and guide them to the afterlife. Its form had been influenced by the energy of Mt. Coronet.

HSAMUROTT.name: H. Samurott
HSAMUROTT.pokedex: Hard of heart and deft of blade, its turbulent blows crash into foes like ceaseless pounding waves.

HDECIDUEYE.name: H. Decidueye
HDECIDUEYE.pokedex: The air stored inside the rachises of Decidueye's feathers insulated the Pokémon against Hisui's extreme cold.

HBRAVIARY.name: H. Braviary
HBRAVIARY.pokedex: Screaming a bloodcurdling battle cry, this huge and ferocious bird Pokémon went out on the hunt.

HSLIGGOO.name: H. Sliggoo
HSLIGGOO.pokedex: A creature given to melancholy. I suspect its metallic shell developed as a result of the mucus on its skin reacting with the iron in Hisui's water.

HGOODRA.name: H. Goodra
HGOODRA.pokedex: Able to freely control the hardness of its metallic shell. It loathes solitude and is extremely clingy-it will fume and run riot if those dearest to it ever leave its side.

HLILLIGANT.name: H. Lilligant
HLILLIGANT.pokedex: Its well-developed legs were the result of a life spent on mountains covered in deep snow. The scent it exudes from its flower crown heartens those in proximity.

HAVALUGG.name: H. Avalugg
HAVALUGG.pokedex: This Pokémon barrels along steep mountain paths, cleaving through the deep snow with its hard icy armor.

HGROWLITHE.name: H. Growlithe
HGROWLITHE.pokedex: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

HARCANINE.name: H. Arcanine
HARCANINE.pokedex: Its magnificent bark conveys a sense of majesty. Anyone hearing it can't help but grovel before it.

HSNEASEL.name: H. Sneasel
HSNEASEL.pokedex: Its sturdy, curved claws are ideal for traversing precipitous cliffs. From the tips of these claws drips a nerve-destroying venom.

SNEASLER.name: Sneasler
SNEASLER.pokedex: Because of Sneasler's virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on frozen highlands.

HVOLTORB.name: H. Voltorb
HVOLTORB.pokedex: When excited, it discharges the electric current it has stored in its belly, then lets out a great, uproarious laugh.

HELECTRODE.name: H. Electrode
HELECTRODE.pokedex: The tissue on the surface of its body is curiously similar in composition to an Apricorn.

HZORUA.name: H. Zorua
HZORUA.pokedex: A once-departed soul, returned to life. Derives power from resentment, which rises as energy atop its head and takes on the forms of foes.

HZOROARK.name: H. Zoroark
HZOROARK.pokedex: It likes to settle grudges and fulfill final wishes. It does so to ensure peaceful passage to the afterlife.

HQWILFISH.name: H. Qwilfish
HQWILFISH.pokedex: Fishers detest this troublesome Pokémon because it sprays poison from its spines, getting it everywhere.

OVERQWIL.name: Overqwil
OVERQWIL.pokedex: Its lancelike spikes and savage temperament have earned it the nickname "sea fiend." It slurps up poison to nourish itself.

ENAMORUS.name: Enamorus
ENAMORUS.pokedex: According to legend, this Pokémon's love gave rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.

ANNIHILAPE.name: Annihilape
ANNIHILAPE.pokedex: When its anger rose beyond a critical point, this Pokémon gained power that is unfettered by the limits of its physical body.

FARIGIRAF.name: Farigiraf
FARIGIRAF.pokedex: Now that the brain waves from the head and tail are synced up, the psychic power of this Pokémon is 10 times stronger than Girafarig’s.

DUDUNSPARCE.name: Dudunsparce
DUDUNSPARCE.pokedex: This Pokémon uses its hard tail to make its nest by boring holes into bedrock deep underground. The nest can reach lengths of over six miles.

DUDUDUNSPARCE.name: Dududunsparce
DUDUDUNSPARCE.pokedex: The gentle Dududunsparce will put Pokémon that wander into its nest onto its back and carry them to the entrance.

KINGAMBIT.name: Kingambit
KINGAMBIT.pokedex: Only a Bisharp that stands above all others in its vast army can evolve into Kingambit.

MZANGOOSE.name: M. Zangoose
MZANGOOSE.pokedex: Even being bisected by a Seviper's tail couldn't quell its rage. It attacks enemies on a physical and spiritual level simultaneously.

MSENTRET.name: M. Sentret
MSENTRET.pokedex: The eye on its stomach enables its psychic powers and never blinks. Dirt and dust are telekinetically repelled.

MFURRET.name: M. Furret
MFURRET.pokedex: It burrows at night, leaving only the eye on its stomach exposed. The eye will stare into space while the rest of it sleeps.

MSEVIPER.name: M. Seviper
MSEVIPER.pokedex: Its iron body is impenetrable to nearly all attacks. When coiled, it can fire metal projectiles using magnetic induction.

MTANGELA.name: M. Tangela
MTANGELA.pokedex: Though it looks like a plant, its green color comes from its jade scales. Looking into its eyes is said to bring three years of bad luck.

MTANGROWTH.name: M. Tangrowth
MTANGROWTH.pokedex: While the snakes covering it are hard as granite, its skin is soft. Predators attacking its unprotected limbs have to contend with its powerful digging claws.

MVULPIX.name: M. Vulpix
MVULPIX.pokedex: It constantly demands treats and gifts from its Trainer. An expensive and fashionable hoard is necessary for evolution.

MNINETALES.name: M. Ninetales
MNINETALES.pokedex: The gifts it received have become a tail of golden light. It weaponizes pure avaricious energy in battle, gaining in power as it is pampered.

MSINISTEA.name: M. Sinistea
MSINISTEA.pokedex: It spends days relaxing on the beach. Its rest is often interrupted by someone who confuses it for a drink.

MPOLTEAGEIST.name: M. Polteageist
MPOLTEAGEIST.pokedex: Despite its refreshing scent, those who drink of its colorful liquid are swiftly put into a deep sleep.

MWURMPLE.name: M. Wurmple
MWURMPLE.pokedex: Its horns efficiently regulate its body temperature. It seeks out Fire- and Ice-type predators to charge itself with energy for evolution.

MSILCOON.name: M. Silcoon
MSILCOON.pokedex: Its silk makes it blend in with snowy rocks. If attacked, its only recourse is to make itself unappetizing by chilling its own body.

MBEAUTIFLY.name: M. Beautifly
MBEAUTIFLY.pokedex: It is less hostile than the Hoennian form, but vicious towards former predators. Its mouthparts inject a fluid similar to liquid nitrogen.

MCASCOON.name: M. Cascoon
MCASCOON.pokedex: Its flame is kept burning by an organ similar to a Bunsen burner. Curious Pokémon often try to put it out, to no avail.

MDUSTOX.name: M. Dustox
MDUSTOX.pokedex: Its abdomen is actually a sophisticated torch drive. Their migrations can be tracked by following broken trees left by supersonic flybys.

MROGGENROLA.name: M. Roggenrola
MROGGENROLA.pokedex: It was first unearthed in forbidden lands. Its body doesn't abide by the physical laws of this universe.

MBOLDORE.name: M. Boldore
MBOLDORE.pokedex: It is more comfortable in alien dimensions than on Earth. The rocky parts of its body can't be analyzed by modern science.

MGIGALITH.name: M. Gigalith
MGIGALITH.pokedex: They can't be understood or predicted, making them dangerous opponents. At the end of their lifespan they return to their home universe, reporting to a higher will.

MHOOTHOOT.name: M. Hoothoot
MHOOTHOOT.pokedex: Its down insulates it against any cold. In winter it will lay dormant beneath snow banks, only to pop out during spring.

MNOCTOWL.name: M. Noctowl
MNOCTOWL.pokedex: When its shadow passes over someone, they feel a horrible chill. Some Trainers find it invigorating.

MGOLDEEN.name: M. Goldeen
MGOLDEEN.pokedex: They obsessively count the pebbles in their rivers, becoming irate if the result is an unlucky number.

MSEAKING.name: M. Seaking
MSEAKING.pokedex: Fearsome Pokémon lining a river in a grand procession is a sign of a Makyan Seaking. They offer endless blessings in exchange for servitude.

MPETILIL.name: M. Petilil
MPETILIL.pokedex: It seems to pride itself on living in inhospitable conditions. If others take up residence nearby, it will move to even colder climes.

MLILLIGANT.name: M. Lilligant
MLILLIGANT.pokedex: It utters royal proclamations and tyrannical edicts on a whim, becoming petulant when its disobedient subjects can't understand it.

MCARNIVINE.name: M. Carnivine
MCARNIVINE.pokedex: It hunts other nocturnal predators, trapping them with its sticky tendrils. Its maniacal laugh is a common sound on autumn nights.

MVULLABY.name: M. Vullaby
MVULLABY.pokedex: It stomps on smaller opponents with its powerful legs, sometimes toppling in the process. If its house is broken, terrible wailing emits until it is repaired.

MMANDIBUZZ.name: M. Mandibuzz
MMANDIBUZZ.pokedex: It steeps the remains of prey within the jar it protects, stirring the concoction with its claws. Folklore says its soul is kept within the diseased mass.

MMUNNA.name: M. Munna
MMUNNA.pokedex: When a Munna egg is placed in the care of a brooding dragon, it hatches into this form. It will repeatedly headbutt Togepi if placed near one.

MMUSHARNA.name: M. Musharna
MMUSHARNA.pokedex: Excess psychic energy is vented as smoke from the hole where its gem once was. Its heart functions as a second brain that lets it communicate telepathically.

MFRILLISH.name: M. Frillish
MFRILLISH.pokedex: They are drawn to mysterious machinery and internet influencers. Because of this, they are common in online horror media.

MJELLICENT.name: M. Jellicent
MJELLICENT.pokedex: They led explorers to an ancient sunken city in the abyss. Its people had uploaded their minds into machines that slowly failed over the ages.

PORYGONMAV.name: Porygon-MAV
PORYGONMAV.pokedex: Rely on LuxTech's literal firewall! Featuring a unique* typing and cutting-edge network threat purgation protocols, this innovative new form has your back.

MAROMATISSE.name: M. Aromatisse
MAROMATISSE.pokedex: It uses both white and black magic. It harvests the flowers that grow on witches who regularly walk between life and death.

PIKACHU.pokedex: Whenever Pikachu comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it's evidence that this Pokémon mistook the intensity of its charge.
Whenever Pikachu comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it's evidence that this Pokémon mistook the intensity of its charge.
Whenever Pikachu comes across something new, it blasts it with a jolt of electricity. If you come across a blackened berry, it's evidence that this Pokémon mistook the intensity of its charge.
